    "created_at": "2019-01-21T08:32:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2019-01-21T08:32:28Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Is it a big hardship to use the extra --?\r\n\r\nYes. They can not be used in shebang, which means you can not have executable `.ipy` script:\r\n```\r\n$ cat xxx.ipy \r\n#!/usr/bin/env ipython3 --\r\n\r\n!echo \"XXX\"\r\n$ ipython3 xxx.ipy \r\nXXX\r\n$ chmod +x xxx.ipy \r\n$ ./xxx.ipy \r\n/usr/bin/env: ‘ipython3 --’: No such file or directory\r\n$ /usr/bin/env ipython3 --version\r\n5.5.0\r\n```\r\n\r\n`.ipy` script popularity is a cause and effect problem. Without command line arguments they are less useful than plain `.py` or `.sh`."
  },
